Mr. Chandler,

Per the Milwaukee Historic Preservation Commission review held on
September 23, 2026, the Certificate of Appropriateness for permit
BV-2026-0438 has been AMENDED. The following two changes apply
effective immediately and supersede any earlier guidance or
estimate-side material plan you may have prepared.

1. CONDUIT FINISH (FIRST FLOOR, VISIBLE RUNS)
   All visible interior conduit on the first floor must be EMT in
   oil-rubbed bronze finish. Standard galvanized EMT is no longer
   approved for visible first-floor runs. The dining-room wainscoting
   bay is exempt and may use concealed standard EMT.

2. WALL PENETRATIONS (FIRST FLOOR)
   Existing plaster walls may NOT be cut for new electrical boxes in
   the following rooms:
     - Room 1A (front parlor)
     - Room 1B (rear parlor)
     - Stair hall
   New circuits in these rooms must be installed either by fishing
   behind base and crown molding, or by surface-mounting in
   period-correct raceway.

3. SWITCH PLATES AND DEVICE FINISH
   Decora-style switch covers are not approved for first-floor visible
   locations. Satin-brass toggle is the only approved switch finish on
   the first floor.

Please acknowledge receipt of this amendment by reply email. Any work
performed under permit BV-2026-0438 that does not comply with the
amended conditions will require remediation at the contractor's expense.

The rough-in inspection slot remains as previously scheduled by the
electrical inspector's office.

